    "Note that the dependence of Σ η on the covariance parameters Θ = (Θ 1,.",
    ", Θ p) has been suppressed for clarity.",
    "Bayesian SVC By assigning independent priors to the parameters in the model defined in Equation (9), we obtain the following Bayesian formulation:",
    "Posterior inference for the parameters can be performed using standard Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) methods (Robert et al., 1999), since the model remains a Gaussian process with a structured covariance matrix.",
    "However, in practice, for large numbers of observations (n) and/or predictors (p), the computational burden becomes substantial."
